HEADWORD: Perdix
<hw>Per"dix</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r"d⟦icr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[L., a partridge, Gr. <grk>pe`rdix</grk>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A genus of birds including the common European partridge. Formerly
the word was used in a much wider sense to include many allied
genera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

